history.content:
186 and 189 are extremely light workload classes. I've never taken 162 but I heard it's ok as long as you get a good team. 198 obviously depends on which DeCal you are taking, but you should be fine with that schedule. One other thing, I don't recommend taking 162 unless you have a good team in mind beforehand. If you are planning on just looking on Piazza or whatever for partners, it might not be worth the risk if you can afford to take it in a later semester.

(2nd opinion): Most people I know, including me, thought 189 was actually a lot of work.  Agree about 186.

(3rd opinion) I don't know where the first Anon commenter got that idea, but 189 is supposed to be a extremely heavy workload. Christopher Hunn stressed that in a meeting I had with him about a possible schedule involving it. 

(4th opinion) I don't recommend taking all 3 of those at once. 162 and 189 together is quite doable though.

(5th opinion) I took 162 and 189 last semester along with two other technical classes.  It's doable, but 189 (at least in the most recent rendition) was a difficult course with a typical homework assignment taking 20-30 hours to complete over a 10 day period.
